Note:
Runa Standard Library: Decimal Module

Provides comprehensive decimal arithmetic and precision control, supporting arbitrary precision,
rounding modes, context management, error handling, and AI/agent-friendly interfaces.

Features:
- Arbitrary precision decimal arithmetic
- All basic and advanced operations (+, -, *, /, **, sqrt, log, exp, etc.)
- Rounding modes (ROUND_HALF_UP, ROUND_HALF_EVEN, ROUND_UP, ROUND_DOWN, etc.)
- Context management (precision, rounding, traps)
- Conversion to/from strings, floats, integers
- Error handling (overflow, underflow, division by zero, invalid operation)
- Financial arithmetic (compound interest, amortization, present value, future value)
- AI/agent-friendly interfaces
:End Note

Note: Core Types and Constants
Type Decimal is Dictionary with:
    value as String
    precision as Integer
    sign as Integer
    exponent as Integer
    context as DecimalContext
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type DecimalContext is Dictionary with:
    precision as Integer defaults to 28
    rounding as String defaults to "ROUND_HALF_EVEN"
    traps as List[String]
    clamp as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type DecimalResult is:
    | DecimalSuccess with value as Decimal
    | DecimalError with message as String and code as String

Type DecimalOptions is Dictionary with:
    context as DecimalContext
    ai_mode as Boolean defaults to false

Note: Rounding Mode Constants
Let ROUND_UP be "ROUND_UP"
Let ROUND_DOWN be "ROUND_DOWN"
Let ROUND_HALF_UP be "ROUND_HALF_UP"
Let ROUND_HALF_DOWN be "ROUND_HALF_DOWN"
Let ROUND_HALF_EVEN be "ROUND_HALF_EVEN"
Let ROUND_CEILING be "ROUND_CEILING"
Let ROUND_FLOOR be "ROUND_FLOOR"

Note: Error Code Constants
Let ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION be "INVALID_OPERATION"
Let ERROR_DIVISION_BY_ZERO be "DIVISION_BY_ZERO"
Let ERROR_OVERFLOW be "OVERFLOW"
Let ERROR_UNDERFLOW be "UNDERFLOW"
Let ERROR_INEXACT be "INEXACT"

Note: Core Decimal Functions
Process called "create_decimal" that takes value as String and context as DecimalContext returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let parsed be parse_decimal_string with value as value
        If parsed is None:
            Return DecimalError with message as "Invalid decimal format: " plus value and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION
        Let (sign, integer_part, fractional_part, exponent) be parsed
        Let decimal_value be normalize_decimal with sign as sign and integer_part as integer_part and fractional_part as fractional_part and exponent as exponent
        Let result be Decimal with:
            value as decimal_value
            precision as context.precision
            sign as sign
            exponent as exponent
            context as context
            metadata as dictionary containing
        Return DecimalSuccess with value as result
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error creating decimal: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "from_float" that takes value as Float and context as DecimalContext returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let string_value be float_to_string with value as value
        Return create_decimal with value as string_value and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error converting float to decimal: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "from_integer" that takes value as Integer and context as DecimalContext returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let string_value be integer_to_string with value as value
        Return create_decimal with value as string_value and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error converting integer to decimal: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "to_string" that takes decimal as Decimal returns String:
    Return format_decimal with decimal as decimal and precision as decimal.precision

Process called "to_float" that takes decimal as Decimal returns Float:
    Try:
        Let string_value be to_string with decimal as decimal
        Return parse_float with string as string_value
    Catch:
        Return 0.0

Process called "to_integer" that takes decimal as Decimal returns Integer:
    Try:
        Let string_value be to_string with decimal as decimal
        Let float_value be parse_float with string as string_value
        Return floor with x as float_value
    Catch:
        Return 0

Note: Arithmetic Operations
Process called "add" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be a.context
        Let a_value be parse_float with string as a.value
        Let b_value be parse_float with string as b.value
        Let result_value be a_value plus b_value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in addition: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "subtract" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be a.context
        Let a_value be parse_float with string as a.value
        Let b_value be parse_float with string as b.value
        Let result_value be a_value minus b_value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in subtraction: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "multiply" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be a.context
        Let a_value be parse_float with string as a.value
        Let b_value be parse_float with string as b.value
        Let result_value be a_value multiplied by b_value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in multiplication: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "divide" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be a.context
        Let a_value be parse_float with string as a.value
        Let b_value be parse_float with string as b.value
        If b_value is equal to 0.0:
            Return DecimalError with message as "Division by zero" and code as ERROR_DIVISION_BY_ZERO
        Let result_value be a_value divided by b_value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in division: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "power" that takes base as Decimal and exponent as Integer returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be base.context
        Let base_value be parse_float with string as base.value
        Let result_value be base_value to the power of exponent
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in power operation: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "sqrt" that takes decimal as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        If value is less than 0.0:
            Return DecimalError with message as "Cannot compute square root of negative number" and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION
        Let result_value be square root of value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in square root: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "log" that takes decimal as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        If value is less than or equal to 0.0:
            Return DecimalError with message as "Cannot compute logarithm of non-positive number" and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION
        Let result_value be natural logarithm of value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in logarithm: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "exp" that takes decimal as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        Let result_value be e to the power of value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in exponential: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Note: Comparison Operations
Process called "compare" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns Integer:
    Try:
        Let a_value be parse_float with string as a.value
        Let b_value be parse_float with string as b.value
        If a_value is less than b_value:
            Return negative 1
        Otherwise if a_value is greater than b_value:
            Return 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
    Catch:
        Return 0

Process called "is_equal" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns Boolean:
    Return compare with a as a and b as b is equal to 0

Process called "is_less_than" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns Boolean:
    Return compare with a as a and b as b is less than 0

Process called "is_greater_than" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns Boolean:
    Return compare with a as a and b as b is greater than 0

Process called "is_less_than_or_equal" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns Boolean:
    Let comparison be compare with a as a and b as b
    Return comparison is less than or equal to 0

Process called "is_greater_than_or_equal" that takes a as Decimal and b as Decimal returns Boolean:
    Let comparison be compare with a as a and b as b
    Return comparison is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Rounding Operations
Process called "round" that takes decimal as Decimal and places as Integer returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        Let factor be 10 to the power of places
        Let rounded_value be round with x as value multiplied by factor divided by factor
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as rounded_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in rounding: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "round_with_mode" that takes decimal as Decimal and places as Integer and mode as String returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        Let factor be 10 to the power of places
        Let scaled_value be value multiplied by factor
        Let rounded_scaled be apply_rounding_mode with value as scaled_value and mode as mode
        Let result_value be rounded_scaled divided by factor
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in rounding with mode: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "floor" that takes decimal as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        Let result_value be floor of value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in floor: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "ceil" that takes decimal as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        Let result_value be ceiling of value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in ceiling: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "trunc" that takes decimal as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be decimal.context
        Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
        Let result_value be truncate value
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in truncate: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Note: Financial Arithmetic
Process called "compound_interest" that takes principal as Decimal and rate as Decimal and time as Decimal and periods as Integer returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be principal.context
        Let p be parse_float with string as principal.value
        Let r be parse_float with string as rate.value
        Let t be parse_float with string as time.value
        Let n be periods
        Let result_value be p multiplied by (1.0 plus r divided by n) to the power of (n multiplied by t)
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in compound interest: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "present_value" that takes future_value as Decimal and rate as Decimal and time as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be future_value.context
        Let fv be parse_float with string as future_value.value
        Let r be parse_float with string as rate.value
        Let t be parse_float with string as time.value
        Let result_value be fv divided by (1.0 plus r) to the power of t
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in present value: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "future_value" that takes present_value as Decimal and rate as Decimal and time as Decimal returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be present_value.context
        Let pv be parse_float with string as present_value.value
        Let r be parse_float with string as rate.value
        Let t be parse_float with string as time.value
        Let result_value be pv multiplied by (1.0 plus r) to the power of t
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in future value: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Process called "amortization_payment" that takes principal as Decimal and rate as Decimal and periods as Integer returns DecimalResult:
    Try:
        Let context be principal.context
        Let p be parse_float with string as principal.value
        Let r be parse_float with string as rate.value
        Let n be periods
        If r is equal to 0.0:
            Return DecimalError with message as "Rate cannot be zero for amortization" and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION
        Let monthly_rate be r divided by 12.0
        Let num_payments be n multiplied by 12
        Let rate_factor be (1.0 plus monthly_rate) to the power of num_payments
        Let result_value be p multiplied by monthly_rate multiplied by rate_factor divided by (rate_factor minus 1.0)
        Let result_string be float_to_string with value as result_value
        Return create_decimal with value as result_string and context as context
    Catch error:
        Return DecimalError with message as "Error in amortization payment: " plus error.message and code as ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION

Note: Context Management
Process called "set_context" that takes decimal as Decimal and context as DecimalContext returns Decimal:
    Set decimal.context to context
    Return decimal

Process called "get_context" that takes decimal as Decimal returns DecimalContext:
    Return decimal.context

Process called "create_decimal_context" returns DecimalContext:
    Return DecimalContext with:
        precision as 28
        rounding as ROUND_HALF_EVEN
        traps as list containing
        clamp as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_decimal_context_with_precision" that takes precision as Integer returns DecimalContext:
    Return DecimalContext with:
        precision as precision
        rounding as ROUND_HALF_EVEN
        traps as list containing
        clamp as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_decimal_context_with_rounding" that takes precision as Integer and rounding as String returns DecimalContext:
    Return DecimalContext with:
        precision as precision
        rounding as rounding
        traps as list containing
        clamp as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_decimal_options" returns DecimalOptions:
    Return DecimalOptions with:
        context as create_decimal_context
        ai_mode as false

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "parse_decimal_string" that takes value as String returns Optional[Tuple[Integer, String, String, Integer]]:
    Try:
        Let trimmed be trim_string with string as value
        Let sign be 1
        Let integer_part be ""
        Let fractional_part be ""
        Let exponent be 0
        If length of trimmed is equal to 0:
            Return None
        
        Let start_index be 0
        If trimmed[0] is equal to "-":
            Set sign to negative 1
            Set start_index to 1
        Otherwise if trimmed[0] is equal to "+":
            Set start_index to 1
        
        Let has_decimal_point be false
        Let has_exponent be false
        Let exponent_sign be 1
        Let exponent_value be ""
        
        For i from start_index to length of trimmed minus 1:
            Let char be trimmed[i]
            If char is equal to ".":
                If has_decimal_point:
                    Return None
                Set has_decimal_point to true
            Otherwise if char is equal to "e" or char is equal to "E":
                If has_exponent:
                    Return None
                Set has_exponent to true
                If i plus 1 is less than length of trimmed:
                    If trimmed[i plus 1] is equal to "-":
                        Set exponent_sign to negative 1
                        Set i to i plus 1
                    Otherwise if trimmed[i plus 1] is equal to "+":
                        Set i to i plus 1
            Otherwise if char is digit:
                If has_exponent:
                    Set exponent_value to exponent_value plus char
                Otherwise if has_decimal_point:
                    Set fractional_part to fractional_part plus char
                Otherwise:
                    Set integer_part to integer_part plus char
            Otherwise:
                Return None
        
        If length of integer_part is equal to 0 and length of fractional_part is equal to 0:
            Return None
        
        If length of exponent_value is greater than 0:
            Set exponent to parse_integer with string as exponent_value multiplied by exponent_sign
        
        Return (sign, integer_part, fractional_part, exponent)
    Catch:
        Return None

Process called "normalize_decimal" that takes sign as Integer and integer_part as String and fractional_part as String and exponent as Integer returns String:
    Let result be ""
    If sign is equal to negative 1:
        Set result to "-"
    
    If length of integer_part is equal to 0:
        Set result to result plus "0"
    Otherwise:
        Set result to result plus integer_part
    
    If length of fractional_part is greater than 0:
        Set result to result plus "." plus fractional_part
    
    If exponent is not equal to 0:
        Set result to result plus "e" plus integer_to_string with value as exponent
    
    Return result

Process called "format_decimal" that takes decimal as Decimal and precision as Integer returns String:
    Let value be parse_float with string as decimal.value
    Let factor be 10 to the power of precision
    Let rounded be round with x as value multiplied by factor divided by factor
    Return float_to_string with value as rounded

Process called "apply_rounding_mode" that takes value as Float and mode as String returns Float:
    Match mode:
        When ROUND_UP:
            Return ceiling of value
        When ROUND_DOWN:
            Return floor of value
        When ROUND_HALF_UP:
            Return round with x as value
        When ROUND_HALF_DOWN:
            Let rounded be round with x as value
            If value minus rounded is equal to 0.5:
                Return floor of value
            Otherwise:
                Return rounded
        When ROUND_HALF_EVEN:
            Let rounded be round with x as value
            If value minus rounded is equal to 0.5:
                If rounded modulo 2 is equal to 0:
                    Return rounded
                Otherwise:
                    Return rounded plus 1.0
            Otherwise:
                Return rounded
        When ROUND_CEILING:
            Return ceiling of value
        When ROUND_FLOOR:
            Return floor of value
        Otherwise:
            Return round with x as value

Note: String Conversion Utilities
Process called "float_to_string" that takes value as Float returns String:
    Return value as string

Process called "integer_to_string" that takes value as Integer returns String:
    Return value as string

Process called "parse_float" that takes string as String returns Float:
    Return string as float

Process called "parse_integer" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Return string as integer

Process called "trim_string" that takes string as String returns String:
    Return string with leading and trailing whitespace removed

Note: Optional Type Support
Process called "Some" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Wrap value in Optional type - CRITICAL for type system correctness
    Return Optional with value as value and has_value as true

Process called "None" returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Return empty Optional type - CRITICAL for type system correctness
    Return Optional with value as none and has_value as false